# Quiz Engine

The Quiz Engine is the active assessment system of LexMastery.

It tests knowledge in real time.

---

# Product Vision

The Quiz Engine must:

- Reinforce learning through testing
- Provide instant feedback
- Adapt difficulty dynamically
- Explain every answer
- Track performance over time

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

QuizController (Riverpod)

↓

QuizState

↓

QuizRepository

↓

Question Engine (API + Local)

---

# State Management

QuizState includes:

- loading
- active
- submitting
- completed
- reviewing
- error

Core Data:

- questions
- currentQuestionIndex
- score
- answers
- timeRemaining
- difficultyLevel

---

# Quiz Types

1. Practice Quiz
2. Timed Quiz
3. Topic Quiz
4. Adaptive Quiz
5. Revision Quiz

---

# Question Types

- Multiple Choice (MCQ)
- True/False
- Scenario-based (Legal reasoning)
- Case application questions

---

# Scoring System

- Correct answer = full score
- Partial scoring (future)
- Time bonus (optional)
- Difficulty weighting

---

# Adaptive Logic

AI adjusts:

- difficulty
- question type
- topic focus

based on performance history.

---

# Timing Rules

Timed quizzes:

- strict countdown
- auto-submit on expiry
- pause only in allowed mode

---

# Offline Behaviour

Quizzes can be:

- preloaded
- taken offline
- synced after completion

AI adaptive mode requires internet.

---

# API Contracts

GET /quizzes

GET /quizzes/{id}

POST /quizzes/submit

GET /quizzes/results/{id}

---

# Analytics Events

quiz_start

quiz_answer_selected

quiz_submit

quiz_complete

quiz_review_open

---

# UI Composition Rules

Quiz UI must include:

- question card
- options list
- timer (if timed)
- progress indicator
- explanation panel

---

# UX Rules

- one question per screen
- no distractions
- immediate feedback in practice mode
- delayed feedback in exam mode

---

# Error Handling

- preserve answers on failure
- allow retry submission
- fallback to cached questions

---

# Performance

- question load <200ms
- smooth transitions between questions

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen readers for questions
- keyboard navigation
- readable option grouping

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Quiz scoring logic

Adaptive engine

State transitions

Widget Tests:

Quiz screen

Question rendering

Timer UI

Integration Tests:

Full quiz lifecycle

Offline quiz flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating quiz features:

- always enforce one-question-per-screen rule
- always implement scoring logic
- always include explanation system
- always support offline quizzes
- never skip result review flow